&lt;h1&gt;Highly Specialist Cardiac Physiologist/Specialist Healthcare Scientist in Echocardiography – Cardiology – Band 7 &lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Part time Fixed term 1 year post (Maternity Cover) &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you looking for a challenge, excellent learning opportunities, and no two days the same? &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Then come and join The Cardiology Department here at the Royal United Hospital. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a Band 7 Specialist Physiologist/Healthcare Scientist to join our enthusiastic busy team here are the Cardiac Centre. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will need to have experience and knowledge &lt;strong&gt;with a&lt;/strong&gt; specialist interest and BSE qualification in echocardiography.   &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The department runs Physiologist/Healthcare Scientist led complex Echo service – including DSE, Bubble and LVO studies and are developing Scientist led TOE, our department also offers a full range of Cardiological diagnostics both invasive and non-invasive.&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is a Part-time 1 year fixed term vacancy for a suitably qualified enthusiastic person to join our team of physiologists within the Cardiac Centre.  Our current working pattern within the department will include occasional weekends.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further info email James Willis james.willis@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
